run
yarn init -y

To start project

## For type-graphql,..

yarn add @typegoose/typegoose apollo-server-core apollo-server-express class-validator cors dotenv express 
graphql@15.3.0 jsonwebtoken mongoose morgan reflect-metadata type-graphql typescript

yarn add -D ts-node @types/express @types/express @types/socket.io @types/node @types/cors @types/dotenv @types/morgan

## Otherwise:
yarn add typescript express cors dotenv morgan

yarn add -D ts-node @types/express @types/express @types/socket.io @types/node @types/cors @types/dotenv @types/morgan


run 
npx tsc --init

copy contents of tsconfig.json to the generated one or just change it appropriately.

In package.json
Add: 
"type": "commonjs",
"start": "node ./build/index.js",
"build": "tsc -p .",
"dev": "nodemon ./src/index.ts"


To get jwt keys:
1. search generate public and private key online. Get the 2 keys.
2. search base64 online and encode the keys then they can be used in .env

